1. d4 b5 2. e3 Bb7 3. Nf3 a6 4. Bd3 Nf6 5. Nbd2 e6 6. O-O c5 7. c3 c4 8. Bc2 d5
$2 {This is a very weak move, imprisoning Black's lightsquare Bishop and
yielding the e5 square to White's pieces without a fight. No doubt Black
thought that the compensating virtue of taking control of e4 was worth these
concessions. But it is not.} 9. Ne5 Bd6 10. f4 O-O 11. g4 {
The standard plan in action.} 11... Nfd7 12. g5 f6 $2 {
Too slow. Now a little accurate calcuation gives White everything he needs.}
13. Bxh7+ $1 Kxh7 14. Qh5+ Kg8 15. g6 $1 {
The standard trick, locking the door on the Black King.} 15... Rf7 16. Nxf7 Qc7
17. Qh8# 1-0

